    It is also possible to create a personal distribution lists so that, for
    instance, you can send mail to cohorts or a defined group of people. Such
    lists can be defined by placing a line such as the following:

    alias cohorts bill ozalp jkf mark kridle@ucbcory

    in the file ..mmaaiillrrcc in your home directory. The current list of such
    aliases can be displayed with the aalliiaass command in mmaaiillxx(1). In mail you
    send, personal aliases will be expanded in mail sent to others so that
    they will be able to rreeppllyy to the recipients.

    The mmaaiillxx(1) utility includes a number of options that can be set in the
    ..mmaaiillrrcc file to alter its behavior; thus set askcc enables the askcc
    feature. (These options are summarized later in this topic.)

